The article discusses the importance of combating hate and discrimination in America, particularly against transgender individuals. It highlights the Transgender Day of Remembrance, which serves as a reminder of the 26 transgender Americans who lost their lives this year. The article acknowledges that the actual number of victims is likely higher, with a majority being women of color. The administration mentioned in the article claims to have taken steps to protect the rights and safety of transgender and LGBTQI+ individuals. These actions include lifting the ban on transgender individuals serving in the military and signing executive actions to strengthen civil rights protections. Additionally, the Department of Homeland Security, with support from other departments, has established the LGBTQI+ Community Safety Partnership to provide safety resources. The article concludes by emphasizing the need to continue fighting against discrimination and ensuring that all Americans can live free from such prejudice.